Communication Hub

We have several ways that students, parents, and community members can get all of the latest information about things going on at Del Oro High School.

----------

Social Media - Follow us on Facebook and Del Oro's main Instagram page for updates about events, sports scores, and happenings around campus. Each class has its own Instagram too! Click here.

----------

Principal Messages & Newsletters - Weekly emails from the principal will keep you engaged and excited about our campus. Longer Newsletters with detailed information about events and opportunities are sent each month. Check out the recent archives of Principal Messages and Newsletters.

----------

Del Oro Student News - Our student news team runs a daily live news show on YouTube every day at 8:30am!

----------

School Calendar - Check the Google Calendars for Activities, Athletics, and All School Events.

----------

Class Reminds - Students sign up for "Activities Reminds" based on their grad year. These "Reminds" are a chance for us to send quick info about dance bids, rallies, lunch activities, etc. "Counseling Reminds" will keep you informed of grade-level guidance, college visits, scholarships, and more.

----------

The Potty Press - The Potty Press is a weekly publication taped on the wall in every restroom on campus. Check the weather, read the joke of the week, and get info about clubs, events, and athletics. See the archives so you can enjoy the potty press at home.
